Tom, I have added you as a cc on this ticket. Story so far:
- Zara raised an issue several months ago with image editing in sports pages;
- We spent some time looking at it but could not find a satisfactory resolution;
- Zara asked us to come up with a time estimate for solving the issue, which we did not do after which the issue got parked;
- Last month, we spotted the ticket and updated it with a couple of suggestions for workarounds;
- This month I brazenly attempted to close the ticket with the inevitable response from Liz.

It would be very helpful if you could give us some guidance on how high a priority addressing this issue is likely to be and how you would like us to proceed.

In particular, is this issue currently a problem for CMS users; are you expecting a larger number of people to be accessing the CMS without access to Firefox over the next 10 months or so; and is the suggestion of refactoring the page likely to be a solution that you are interested in?

Many thanks.

